{"name": "mitba", "metadata": {"name": "mitba", "version": "1.1.1", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7"], "home_page": "https://github.com/Infinidat/mitba", "license": "BSD3", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["flux", "Logbook"], "summary": "Python library for caching results from functions and methods", "upload_time": 1565703107}, "documentation": ["Mitba\n=====\n\n|                       |                                                                                    |\n|-----------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| Build Status          | ![Build Status](https://secure.travis-ci.org/Infinidat/mitba.png ) |\n| Supported Versions    | ![Supported Versions](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-2.7%2C3.5%2C3.6%2C3.7-green.svg)    |\n| Latest Version        | ![Latest Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/mitba.svg)                  |\n\n\n`mitba` is a small library for implementing method or function-level caching for results.\n\n* [Documentation](https://mitba.readthedocs.io/en/latest/)\n\n\nLicence\n-------\nBSD3\n\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "mitba.python_compat", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "mitba.python_compat.wraps", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "wrapped", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["a convenience function on top of functools.wraps:\n\n- adds the original function to the wrapped function as __wrapped__ attribute."]}, {"name": "mitba.python_compat.iteritems", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "d", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mitba.python_compat.iteritems", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "d", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "mitba.python_compat._PY2", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mitba.python_compat.wraps", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "mitba", "documentation": ["Adapted from", "http://wiki.python.org/moin/PythonDecoratorLibrary#Cached_Properties"], "functions": [{"name": "mitba.ignoring_cache", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mitba._get_instancemethod_cache_entry", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "method_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mitba.cached_method", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Decorator that caches a method's return value each time it is called.\nIf called later with the same arguments, the cached value is returned, and\nnot re-evaluated."]}, {"name": "mitba._get_function_cache_entry", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mitba.cached_function", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Decorator that caches a function's return value each time it is called.\nIf called later with the same arguments, the cached value is returned, and\nnot re-evaluated."]}, {"name": "mitba.clear_cache", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mitba.clear_cached_entry", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mitba.populate_cache", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "attributes_to_skip", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["this method attempts to get all the lazy cached properties and methods\nThere are two special cases:\n\n- Some attributes may not be available and raises exceptions.\n  If you wish to skip these, pass them in the attributes_to_skip list\n- The calling of cached methods is done without any arguments, and catches TypeError exceptions\n  for the case a cached method requires arguments. The exception is logged."]}], "variables": [{"name": "mitba._logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mitba._local_caching", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mitba._cached_method_id_allocator", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "mitba._Local", "bases": ["threading.local"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "mitba._Local.enabled", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "mitba.cached_property", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "mitba.cached_property.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fget", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "doc", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mitba.cached_property.__get__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "inst", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "owner", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Decorator for read-only properties evaluated only once.\n\nIt can be used to created a cached property like this:\n\n```\nimport random\n\n# the class containing the property must be a new-style class\nclass MyClass(object):\n    # create property whose value is cached for ten minutes\n    @cached_method\n    def randint(self):\n        # will only be evaluated every 10 min. at maximum.\n        return random.randint(0, 100)\n```\n\nThe value is cached in the '\\_\\_mitba_cache\\_\\_' attribute of the object inst that\nhas the property getter method wrapped by this decorator. The '\\_\\_mitba_cache\\_\\_'\nattribute value is a dictionary which has a key for every property of the\nobject which is wrapped by this decorator. Each entry in the cache is\ncreated only when the property is accessed for the first time and is a\ntwo-element tuple with the last computed property value and the last time\nit was updated in seconds since the epoch.\n\nTo expire a cached property value manually just do:\n\n```\ndel inst.__mitba_cache__[<property name>]\n```\n"]}, {"name": "mitba.cached_method_with_custom_cache", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "mitba.cached_method_with_custom_cache.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cache_class", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mitba.cached_method_with_custom_cache.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Decorator that caches a method's return value each time it is called.\nIf called later with the same arguments, the cached value is returned, and\nnot re-evaluated.\ndecorated class must implement inst.init_cache() which creates inst.__mitba_cache__ dictionary."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "mitba.LazyImmutableDict", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "mitba.LazyImmutableDict.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "dict", "type": null, "